<div class="content_wrapper_definitions">
    <div class="definitions_text">There are tons of terms in the Senior Care industry... it can be dificult to know what you should be looking for. <br>Spend a few minutes reading these definitions and you'll soon know the difference between 'Assisted Living' and 'Skilled Nursing.'</div>
    <div class="mCustomScrollbar" data-mcs-theme="dark-thick" id="definitions_results">
        <div id="definition_box" class="definition_box">
            <h2 class="definition_title">Alzheimer&#8217;s or Memory Care Facility </h2>
            <div class="definition_description"><a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=ALZHEIMERS+CARE">Alzheimer&#8217;s or Memory Care Facility</span></a> is a 24-hour licensed long-term care skilled nursing facility that provides room, board, and memory care services to seniors challenged by memory loss.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Assisted Living</h2>
            <div class="definition_description"><a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=ASSISTED+LIVING"><span class='bold'>Assisted Living</span></a> is a licensed residential community for seniors who require assistance with basic activities of daily living that provides assistive and supportive services usually including meals, housekeeping, and activities.  Assisted Living can be covered by private pay and other types of insurance.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Home Health - Medical</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=HOME+HEALTH+-+MEDICAL"><span class='bold'>Home Health - Medical</span></a> provides skilled medical and rehabilitative services by a licensed professional within one&#8217;s home following a recent inpatient stay, or provides additional support for one to remain safely at home and avoid hospitalization. Home health can be covered by Medicare and other types of insurance.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Home Health - Non-Medical</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=HOME+HEALTH+-+NON-MEDICAL"><span class='bold'>Home Health - Non-Medical</span></a> provides basic household help, typically for seniors who are living on their own. These services can include meal preparation help, light house cleaning or tidying up, and in some instances help with bathing and hygiene. These services do not include medical monitoring or nursing care, but can be a good set of eyes to make sure everything is going well. Usually these services are not covered by insurance.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Hospice Care</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=HOSPICE+CARE"><span class='bold'>Hospice Care</span></a> is a type of care and philosophy for someone who has been diagnosed with a life-limiting or terminal illness, under which the patient&#8217;s physical, emotional, and spiritual needs are met. Hospice can be provided wherever one calls home, such as a personal residence, assisted living, nursing home, and many other scenarios. Hospice can be covered through Medicare and other types of insurance.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Nursing Homes</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=NURSING+%26+SKILLED+NURSING+HOMES"><span class='bold'>Nursing Homes</span></a> provide an ongoing variety of custodial services in a 24-hour inpatient licensed nursing facility to help meet both medical and non-medical needs of people with a chronic illness or disability, who cannot care for themselves for long periods of time. Nursing Homes can be covered by private pay and other types of insurance.</div> 
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Skilled Nursing</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=NURSING+%26+SKILLED+NURSING+HOMES"><span class='bold'>Skilled Nursing</span></a> is a specialized treatment program provided in a 24-hour licensed nursing facility for those requiring more custodial and rehabilitative care following a hospital stay. Skilled nursing can be covered through Medicare and other types of insurance.</div>
            <hr>    
            <h2 class="definition_title">Rehabilitation Centers</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=REHABILITATION+CENTERS"><span class='bold'>Rehabilitation Centers</span></a> are specialized licensed facilities dedicated to improving, maintaining, or restoring physical strength, cognition, and mobility with maximized results. Typically, rehabilitation helps people gain greater independence after illness, injury, or surgery.</div>
            <hr>
            <h2 class="definition_title">Retirement & Independent Living</h2>
            <div class="definition_description">
            <a href="<?php echo base_url();?>welcome/results?need=RETIREMENT+%26+INDEPENDENT+LIVING"><span class='bold'>Retirement & Independent Living</span></a> is residential housing designed for older adults who are generally able to care for themselves. Shared services, amenities, activities, and socialization opportunities are often provided.</div>       
         </div> 
